default5.default&#xa0;default&#xa0;default&#xa0;default&#xa0;default&#xa0;default Is sentence length a legally robust basis on which to retain an entitlement to vote?default&#xa0;defaultEMB commentdefaultIf only some serving prisoners are able to register any option is preferred that allows the Court to make a considered decision based on the particular facts of the case, the nature of the offence and the circumstances of the convicted person to be taken into account.  
default&#xa0;
defaultThis follows the guidance given by Judge Caflisch
default (7c; Hirst v UK 2005)
default “The legislation in question must provide that disenfranchisement, as a complementary punishment, is a matter to be decided by the judge, not the executive.”
default&#xa0;
defaultThe
default concern
default of EROs
default is that by not following this guidance we may be no further forward in terms of Human Rights challenges to the register.
